  "poem": {
    "content": "A voyage on vapor, a canvas gray,\nThe ocean breathes a salty spray.\nA mystery unfolds in watery dance,\nWhile shadows shift, a fleeting glance.\n\nA payment due, for passage deep,\nWhere ancient secrets softly sleep.\nAn apple rots, a bitter juice,\nA creeping dread, insidious.\n\nDisease whispers on the breeze,\nRustling pages of the book of trees.\nHe wears a sock, now frayed and thin,\nA drip, drip, drip, where do I begin?\n\nTo understand the tangled thread,\nAround her neck, by sorrow led.\nThe next port calls, a distant shore,\nWhere scattered thoughts will be no more.\n\nTo find a solace in the air,\nAnd watch the world without a care.\nThe dance continues, life’s refrain,\nAmidst the vapor and the rain.",
